                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/9662: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Germany</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morris</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-04-06T15:00:00+02:00"
                            >April 6, 1941—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received April 7—6:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1302. The various documents issued by the Foreign Office today avoid any
                    statement in the nature of declaration of war against Greece <pb facs="0727"
                        n="715" xml:id="pg_715"/> with the exception of the concluding sentence of a
                    memorandum which was attached to the note handed the Greek Minister<note n="99"
                        xml:id="d700fn99">Alexandre Rizo-Rangabé</note> today. The memorandum
                    concludes with this statement. “The Reich Government can no longer close their
                    eyes to the fact that Greece is making common cause with Britain and must
                    therefore be regarded as Germany’s enemy in the present war with all the
                    consequences that this entails.”</p>
                <p>The text of the note to the Greek Minister has not yet been made public. I have
                    an appointment with the Greek Minister this afternoon.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Morris</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
